‚öôÔ∏è 2. Power Connection Overview

Motor Power (7.4 V‚Äì12 V) ‚Üí L298N +12 V

ESP32 Power ‚Üí 5 V pin (from L298N 5 V regulator if stable) or from a separate DC-DC buck converter (7.4 V ‚Üí 5 V).

Grounds must be common ‚Üí Connect ESP32 GND ‚Üî L298N GND ‚Üî Battery ‚Äì.



ü™õ 3. Working Flow

MPU6050 measures tilt and sends data via I¬≤C (GPIO 21 & 22).

ESP32 processes this and runs PID algorithm.

PWM signals from GPIO 25 & 33 control motor speed via L298N.

Bluetooth in ESP32 receives commands from your phone to move Forward/Backward/Left/Right.

Motors correct balance dynamically by adjusting wheel speed.
